                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-30T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 30, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 30—11:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1255. It is my impression that the Soviet mistrust and suspicion of Britain
                    continues, although perhaps somewhat diminished as a result of the exigencies of
                    the situation. At any rate it appears that the British Military Mission is being
                    tolerated rather than fully utilized or informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
